Program: Last Word
Title: Dan Topolski, Lady Villiers, John Davies, Tim Lusty, Clark Terry
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b053c3pn
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 1 Mar 2015
Andrea Catherwood tells the life stories of Dan Topolski the inspirational and at times controversial Oxford University rowing coach; Lady Villiers, a Belgian Resistance leader who spied from inside her family Chateau; Wales's pre-eminent historian and commentator John Davies; Dr Tim Lusty, Oxfam humanitarian whose innovations changed famine relief efforts and jazz musician and stylist Clark Terry. Show less